			<div class="content" id="post-content-4287475">
									

<p>Darkstuff, you absolute madman. You've done it. You've made one of the most unique, interesting, heart-pounding adventures on the wiki.</p>
<p>These characters are honestly my favorite, and even when we only got little bite-sized bits of them, it left me wanting more. More Jerry, more Brahman, more of these amazing people!</p>
<p>I really didn't know what I was getting into when I read that first tale, but oh boy, this story was really unpredictable.</p>
<p>Just&#8230; Wow. I look forward to your next big adventure. Good job, and in case it wasn't clear, +1.</p>
<p>(Also, that epilogue is a nice little sendoff!)</p>
<p>Edit: tacking my reread comment onto this one. I'm&#8230; not too sure on what to say, honestly. This is just an amazing series. We finally get closure on Abraham and Tom, Brahaman is introduced and I somehow instantly like him, and I love how it ends with the same statement that the first tale ended with, almost. I just wonder what Dorer and everyone spends eternity doing. +1, and this is an amazing series.</p>

							</div>

								
